  "prompt": "Why is Mark Zuckerberg supporting digital India? Is there a hidden agenda behind it?",
  "response": "Mark Zuckerberg and Facebook (now Meta) have been supporting Digital India for several potential reasons:\n\n1. Business Expansion:\n- Large potential market of over 1.4 billion people\n- Growing internet and smartphone penetration in India\n- Opportunity to increase Facebook and WhatsApp user base\n\n2. Strategic Economic Interests:\n- Access to emerging digital consumer market\n- Potential for future technological investments\n- Creating partnerships with Indian tech companies\n\n3. Platform Growth:\n- Increasing user engagement and data collection\n- Expanding digital connectivity in rural and urban areas\n- Developing new market opportunities\n\n4. Philanthropic Image:\n- Presenting Facebook as a socially responsible company\n- Supporting digital literacy and technological empowerment\n- Building positive public relations\n\n5. Geopolitical Positioning:\n- Establishing technological presence in a key emerging market\n- Competing with other global tech companies\n\nWhile these objectives suggest potential business motivations, it's not necessarily a purely exploitative agenda. The digital initiatives can also genuinely benefit Indian users by:\n- Improving internet accessibility\n- Providing digital skills training\n- Supporting local entrepreneurship\n- Enhancing technological infrastructure\n\nThe support appears to be a combination of strategic business interests and potential social impact.",
